  "metodologia": "Phytosociological survey using quadrant point method. 199 quadrant points were surveyed across 4 sites, with 10 lines of 50 m perpendicular to trails, spaced 10 m from each other. Every 10 m a point was set on each sampling line. For each sample, distance to apex, circumference at ground level (CGL ≥3 cm), and total height were recorded. All woody individuals meeting inclusion criteria were considered. Plants identified by native names by holders of traditional knowledge. Phytosociological parameters calculated using FITOPAC 1.0 software.",
